results.name: Imaginary part of Gaussian norm-multiply-perfect numbers, in order of increasing norm.
comment: See A332318 (the corresponding real parts) for the definition of Gaussian norm-multiply-perfect numbers.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..182
mathematica: csigma[z_] := DivisorSigma[1, z, GaussianIntegers -> True]; normultPerf[z_] := Divisible[Abs[csigma[z]]^2, Abs[z]^2]; seq = {}; max = 10^2; Do[z = a + b*I; If[Abs[z] <= max && normultPerf[z], AppendTo[seq, {Abs[z]^2, z}]], {a, 1, max}, {b, 0, max}]; Im[Transpose[Sort[seq]][[2]]] (* after _T. D. Noe_ at A102532 *)
results.author: _Amiram Eldar_, Feb 09 2020
